      ],
      "block_index": 17,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0053",
      "text": "Overview",
      "bbox": [
        128.22,
        574.96,
        172.62,
        586.08
      ],
      "block_index": 17,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0054",
      "text": "The Exchange Virtual Fabrics Parameters ELS (EVFP) protocol allows a VF capable N_Port and a",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        598.96,
        539.97,
        610.08
      ],
      "block_index": 18,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0055",
      "text": "VF capable F_Port to:",
      "bbox": [
        96.0,
        610.96,
        193.18,
        622.07
      ],
      "block_index": 18,
      "line_index": 2,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0056",
      "text": "a) Negotiate the VFT Tagging operational mode;",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        635.02,
        325.17,
        646.14
      ],
      "block_index": 19,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0057",
      "text": "b) Verify the consistency of the two Port VF_IDs; and",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        659.02,
        345.17,
        670.13
      ],
      "block_index": 20,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0058",
      "text": "c)",
      "bbox": [
        106.02,
        683.02,
        114.34,
        694.13
      ],
      "block_index": 21,
      "line_index": 1,
      "span_index": 1
    },
    {
      "span_id": "p206_s0059",
      "text": "Establish the list of operational Virtual Fabrics across the link.",
      "bbox": [
